node.text: Joshua Jackson is revealing the untraditional way in which he and wife Jodie Turner-Smith decided to tie the knot. 💍 When asked if he always knew that he and Turner-Smith were "destined" to get married, Jackson said, "I knew the moment she asked me." ❤️ "She asked me, yeah, on New Year's Eve," the Dawsons Creek alum said. "We were walking down the beach, and she asked me to marry her." 🥰 Tap the bio link for the full story. | 📷: David M. Benett/Dave Benett/Getty Images

node.text: Wally Funk finally made it to space! 👏 The 82-year-old trailblazing aviator joined Jeff Bezos on the Amazon billionaire's Blue Origin spaceflight. Funk has been waiting for a chance to head into orbit since the 1960s, when she was part of the Mercury 13, a group of women who tested to become astronauts before their program was later canceled. "I got a hold of NASA four times. I said, 'I want to become an astronaut.' But nobody would take me," she said earlier this month. "I didn't think that I would ever get to go up." Tap the bio link for her story. | 📷: AP/Shutterstock

node.text: Jeff Bezos has made it to space. Bezos alongside his brother and two other history-making companions — 82-year-old Wally Funk and 18-year-old Oliver Daemen — took to the skies Tuesday morning, blasting off in the New Shepard rocket at 8:12 a.m. local time from Launch Site One in Van Horn, Texas. The mission was the first space flight with humans on board for Blue Origin, the aerospace manufacturing and spaceflight company the billionaire founded in 2000. Tap the bio link for the full story. | 📷: BLUE ORIGIN HANDOUT/EPA-EFE/Shutterstock

node.text: Wrangler, a canine who stole hearts and raised awareness of service dogs on The Today Show, has died. He was 6. 💔 The yellow Labrador retriever died on Saturday night, after struggling with liver disease, his handler Saxon Eastman announced on Instagram. "He started a wave of national media coverage for guide and service dogs, he worked as a guide dog, and most importantly, he protected thousands of people everyday as a Connecticut State Police Explosives Detection K9," Eastman wrote. 🙏 Tap the bio link for more. | 📷: Heidi Gutman/NBC/NBC Newswire/NBCUniversal via Getty
